    "body": "### Problem\n\nSome Neovim plugins need to specifically refer to Unicode code points by value.\nFor example, the nvim-web-devicons plugin includes a long table containing Unicode codepoints in the Private Use Area (which by definition cannot be rendered on GitHub). This can be seen [here](https://github.com/nvim-tree/nvim-web-devicons/blob/master/lua/nvim-web-devicons/default/icons_by_filename.lua).\n\nWhile LuaJIT includes the syntax `'\\u{XXXX}'` for the UTF-8 encoding of the code point `U+XXXX`, this syntax is not a part of Lua 5.1. Thus any plugin that needs to convert Unicode code points into UTF-8 would need to write their own version of the function to remain portable.\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe Neovim standard library should provide a function that implements this feature.\nA function such as `vim.str_from_codes` with the same behavior as [`utf8.char`](https://www.lua.org/manual/5.5/manual.html#pdf-utf8.char) would be useful for these kinds of situations.",
